# Facebook Ads-Only Blocklist for Pi-hole
# Created on July 11, 2025
# Description: Blocks domains associated with Facebook ads and tracking, while allowing www.facebook.com for core functionality.
# Note: Test thoroughly to ensure no critical services (e.g., Facebook login, WhatsApp) are disrupted.
# Source: Community-sourced lists and known Facebook ad domains
# Add to Pi-hole via Group Management > Adlists > Add (paste this file's hosted URL or import locally)

ads.facebook.com
an.facebook.com
creative.fb.com
pixel.facebook.com
analytics.facebook.com
adsmanager.facebook.com
tr.facebook.com
badge.facebook.com
*.atdmt.com
*.fbcdn.net
*.fbsbx.com
connect.facebook.net
graph.facebook.com
staticxx.facebook.com
scontent.xx.fbcdn.net
external.xx.fbcdn.net
platform-lookaside.fbsbx.com

# Notes:
# - Excludes www.facebook.com and *.facebook.com to preserve access to the main site and login services.
# - Use Pi-hole's query log to identify additional ad-related domains if ads persist.
# - Whitelist domains like api.facebook.com or whatsapp.net if app functionality breaks.
# - Update this list periodically to capture new ad domains.
